BAYLOR UNIVERSITY FOOTBALL MEDIA CONFERENCE
September 10, 2016
Aiavion Edwards
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
Baylor - 40, SMU - 10   
 Q.  How important is it to have a veteran like Orion back there?  He's been through so much and is such a key player.  
AIAVION EDWARDS: It means a lot.  He's a guy that you can always count on to get us the call -- you know, the coverage call, a guy that's just going to do what he can, a guy that's going to give it all he has every play.   
It's just awesome to have him back there and just to find the ball wherever it's going or to come downhill and make plays.  It's nice.  The experience he brings is just amazing.   
 Q.  His interception for the touchdown, I mean, is that just kind of a veteran just kind of knowing what he's doing out there?  
AIAVION EDWARDS: I think so.  He's just kind of playing.  He kind of figured out.  He knew what was coming, and he was able to make a big play on the ball and take it back.  It's something that comes with experience.  He was able to trust himself and break on the ball and go when he needed to go.   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT